# 3️⃣ Anaconda Cloud Setup

### Step 1: Sign Up for Anaconda Cloud

**Visit the Anaconda Website:**  
Go to the official Anaconda website: [Anaconda](https://www.anaconda.com/).

**Click “Sign Up”:**  
On the homepage, click the **"Sign Up"** button located at the top right of the page.

**Fill Out Your Information:**  
- Enter your **email address**.
- Choose a **username** and **password**.
- Agree to the terms and conditions.
- Click **"Sign Up"** to create your account.

---

### Step 2: Install Anaconda

**Download Anaconda:**  
Go to the [Anaconda Downloads page](https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual) and choose the version suitable for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).

**Install Anaconda:**  
- Run the installer after downloading it.
- Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the installation.
  - **Windows**: Make sure to check the option that adds Anaconda to your system's PATH during installation.
  - **macOS/Linux**: Follow the terminal instructions to install Anaconda.

---

### Step 3: Access Anaconda Cloud

**Login to Anaconda Cloud:**  
After signing up for an account and installing Anaconda, you can access Anaconda Cloud by opening your browser and navigating to [Anaconda Cloud Login](https://anaconda.org/login).

- Enter your **username** and **password** to log in.

---

### Step 4: Set Up Anaconda CLI (Command-Line Interface)

**Install Anaconda CLI (if not already installed):**  
- Open the terminal (macOS/Linux) or Anaconda Prompt (Windows).
- Run the following command to make sure Anaconda is correctly installed:

```bash
conda --version
